rows.label: qst200309_msg0001
rows.name:
Say what?
Did I see a Gogol?

rows.label: qst200309_msg0002
rows.name:
I saw something. But it scared me
senseless, so I didn't dare get up...

rows.label: qst200309_msg0003
rows.name:
Admittedly... I didn't get a proper look,
so I couldn't tell you more about it...

rows.label: qst200309_msg0004
rows.name:
Although come to think of it, it seemed
pretty slight for a Gogol, maybe...?

rows.label: qst200309_msg0005
rows.name:
Still, it's pretty darn rare for a Gogol to
appear in town, you know?

rows.label: qst200309_msg0006
rows.name:
Clever buggers, them Gogols are,
so they usually know better than to
wander into peopled areas.

rows.label: qst200309_msg0007
rows.name:
There's probably some reason for it,
I expect.

rows.label: qst200309_msg0008
rows.name: Now, that's about all I know.

rows.label: qst200309_msg0009
rows.name:
If you need more,
ask some other folks!
